1
00:00:05,880 --> 00:00:06,880
Watch out!

2
00:00:15,530 --> 00:00:16,530
Fuu!

3
00:00:16,530 --> 00:00:17,530
Are you hurt?

4
00:00:20,220 --> 00:00:21,220
Are you okay?

5
00:00:32,600 --> 00:00:36,100
"The Boy Next World My Destiny"
(Episode 3)

6
00:01:17,500 --> 00:01:18,840
Are you sure nothing hurts?

7
00:01:19,480 --> 00:01:20,480
Yeah.

8
00:01:21,410 --> 00:01:22,410
How about here?

9
00:01:24,220 --> 00:01:25,220
Does this hurt?

10
00:01:26,700 --> 00:01:27,700
What about here?

11
00:01:32,120 --> 00:01:33,120
You're really okay?

12
00:01:36,210 --> 00:01:37,210
Sara-senpai...

13
00:01:37,580 --> 00:01:39,090
you're acting just like my mom.

14
00:01:41,440 --> 00:01:42,640
Your mom...?

15
00:01:43,320 --> 00:01:44,320
Yeah.

16
00:01:45,360 --> 00:01:46,570
It brings back memories.

17
00:01:47,610 --> 00:01:48,610
My mom...

18
00:01:48,710 --> 00:01:51,470
She moved to Australia right
after my dad passed away.

19
00:01:53,310 --> 00:01:54,510
I guess she couldn't help it.

20
00:01:55,650 --> 00:01:58,520
She said staying in Japan just
reminded her of him too much.

21
00:01:58,640 --> 00:01:59,960
She used to cry every single day.

22
00:02:01,870 --> 00:02:04,190
So now we mostly just talk on the phone.

23
00:02:05,190 --> 00:02:06,570
It's a little lonely,

24
00:02:06,730 --> 00:02:08,160
but it was my choice.

25
00:02:10,490 --> 00:02:14,430
Did you choose to stay
here to be with your father?

26
00:02:15,870 --> 00:02:16,870
Huh?

27
00:02:19,970 --> 00:02:21,850
Oh...

28
00:02:22,930 --> 00:02:24,920
Did the other Fuu tell you that?

29
00:02:34,820 --> 00:02:36,240
Oh, right.

30
00:02:38,940 --> 00:02:40,040
I've made up my mind.

31
00:02:42,460 --> 00:02:44,440
I'm going to help you
get back to your world.

32
00:02:44,940 --> 00:02:46,140
Back to the person you love.

33
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:15,000
(Fuu: Meeting at 9:00! Don't forget!)

34
00:03:19,270 --> 00:03:22,760
See? The answer was right there.

35
00:03:25,740 --> 00:03:26,740
Yeah.

36
00:03:33,760 --> 00:03:34,860
You're a handsome one.

37
00:03:35,480 --> 00:03:37,260
I bet you've broken quite a few hearts.

38
00:03:37,990 --> 00:03:41,650
You're haunted by the
grudges of many women.

39
00:03:42,760 --> 00:03:44,340
It's quite a serious situation.

40
00:03:44,780 --> 00:03:46,570
Evil spirits? What should he do?

41
00:03:47,210 --> 00:03:48,460
There's only one way.

42
00:03:48,970 --> 00:03:49,970
You...

43
00:03:50,170 --> 00:03:51,640
should move in and live with me.

44
00:03:51,970 --> 00:03:52,660
That way,

45
00:03:52,661 --> 00:03:54,670
I can protect you 24 hours a day.

46
00:03:54,870 --> 00:03:55,870
What do you say?

47
00:03:56,070 --> 00:03:57,470
Sara-senpai, let's get out of here.

48
00:04:00,460 --> 00:04:02,550
If it saves you, it's a
small price to pay, right?

49
00:04:03,020 --> 00:04:04,020
I'm so sorry.

50
00:04:05,320 --> 00:04:07,400
I heard this place was really accurate.

51
00:04:09,110 --> 00:04:10,410
Heard? From who?

52
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:13,950
The reviews online.

53
00:04:22,990 --> 00:04:26,300
I really thought this would help
get you back to your world.

54
00:04:27,870 --> 00:04:28,870
Ugh, I'm so stupid.

55
00:04:32,040 --> 00:04:33,240
I actually had a great time.

56
00:04:37,123 --> 00:04:39,033
Getting to spend the whole day with you.

57
00:05:00,200 --> 00:05:01,390
Hey, Taiga.

58
00:05:01,710 --> 00:05:02,710
Who's that guy?

59
00:05:03,710 --> 00:05:05,410
The one holding hands with Sara.

60
00:05:06,100 --> 00:05:08,340
Are those two dating?

61
00:05:10,470 --> 00:05:11,470
I have no idea.

62
00:05:13,030 --> 00:05:14,030
Why not?

63
00:05:14,590 --> 00:05:16,320
Aren't you the one who looks after him?

64
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:20,070
No, I'm not. Give that back.

65
00:05:20,200 --> 00:05:22,459
But Sara doesn't really talk

66
00:05:22,460 --> 00:05:24,310
to anyone except you, does he?

67
00:05:25,440 --> 00:05:26,800
How did they even end up together?

68
00:05:28,780 --> 00:05:31,770
Who knows.

69
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:37,820
Anyway, that guy owes us an explanation.

70
00:05:40,320 --> 00:05:40,880
Huh?

71
00:05:40,881 --> 00:05:42,260
Well, obviously.

72
00:05:42,280 --> 00:05:44,560
He's hogging our Sara all to himself.

73
00:05:45,820 --> 00:05:47,700
We're counting on you, Taiga.

74
00:05:48,520 --> 00:05:49,600
You're our only hope.

75
00:05:53,560 --> 00:05:54,560
Wait... me?

76
00:05:59,500 --> 00:06:01,610
Alright, alright, what's Fuu up to now?

77
00:06:02,160 --> 00:06:03,530
Where is Fuu Yotsuba?

78
00:06:03,800 --> 00:06:04,800
Is he in class?

79
00:06:05,460 --> 00:06:06,460
I don't know.

80
00:06:07,910 --> 00:06:09,430
Then give me his contact info.

81
00:06:14,950 --> 00:06:15,950
That cloud...

82
00:06:16,480 --> 00:06:17,480
Doesn't it look like a tiger?

83
00:06:17,480 --> 00:06:18,480
It's a lion.

84
00:06:19,370 --> 00:06:20,689
But it doesn't have a mane.

85
00:06:20,690 --> 00:06:22,900
It's a lioness. It doesn't have stripes.

86
00:06:25,283 --> 00:06:26,453
No, it's definitely a tiger.

87
00:06:26,860 --> 00:06:27,860
A tiger.

88
00:06:28,430 --> 00:06:29,750
It's totally a tiger.

89
00:06:29,990 --> 00:06:30,990
Because I said so.

90
00:06:33,460 --> 00:06:34,460
If you say so.

91
00:06:37,810 --> 00:06:39,760
You shouldn't worry so much.

92
00:06:40,130 --> 00:06:42,160
Tiger-senpai.

93
00:06:42,630 --> 00:06:44,230
It's not Tiger.

94
00:06:44,460 --> 00:06:45,460
It's Taiga.

95
00:06:46,070 --> 00:06:47,070
Hey!

96
00:06:47,390 --> 00:06:48,810
Where's Fuu Yotsuba's contact info?

97
00:06:49,690 --> 00:06:50,690
Oh.

98
00:06:53,020 --> 00:06:54,020
Hey!

99
00:06:59,130 --> 00:07:01,040
Be honest with me.

100
00:07:01,910 --> 00:07:03,610
Does Sara have some kind of dirt on you?

101
00:07:04,930 --> 00:07:05,930
Dirt?

102
00:07:06,050 --> 00:07:07,880
Is he threatening you or bullying you?

103
00:07:08,090 --> 00:07:09,330
That's what's happening, right?

104
00:07:09,950 --> 00:07:10,950
I'm sorry.

105
00:07:11,240 --> 00:07:12,400
I'll apologize on his behalf.

106
00:07:13,420 --> 00:07:15,460
I'll have a serious talk with him.

107
00:07:15,790 --> 00:07:17,150
He's not doing anything like that.

108
00:07:20,100 --> 00:07:22,290
Well, that's a relief.

109
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:24,700
That guy...

110
00:07:24,740 --> 00:07:26,780
He's been saying some
really weird stuff lately.

111
00:07:29,310 --> 00:07:30,520
Ah...

112
00:07:30,860 --> 00:07:31,960
You mean...

113
00:07:32,310 --> 00:07:33,970
Like how we're dating?

114
00:07:33,980 --> 00:07:35,640
Yeah, exactly that.

115
00:07:36,110 --> 00:07:37,850
You've never even spoken to him before.

116
00:07:39,360 --> 00:07:42,210
Why would he suddenly start saying that?

117
00:07:44,400 --> 00:07:46,580
Is he okay in the head?

118
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:51,040
Anyway, I'm not being threatened. I'm fine.

119
00:07:52,210 --> 00:07:54,060
Besides, Sara-senpai is a good person.

120
00:07:58,250 --> 00:07:59,720
Sara? A good person?

121
00:08:00,450 --> 00:08:01,450
No way.

122
00:08:02,290 --> 00:08:03,989
If his dad hadn't asked
me to look out for him,

123
00:08:03,990 --> 00:08:06,190
I wouldn't give him the time of day.

124
00:08:06,710 --> 00:08:08,939
He pushes everything onto
others and never apologizes.

125
00:08:08,940 --> 00:08:10,350
He's just an arrogant jerk.

126
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:14,360
How can you say that about him?

127
00:08:23,370 --> 00:08:26,240
Fine, then go ahead and date him.

128
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:29,699
If he has a boyfriend,

129
00:08:29,700 --> 00:08:31,830
then I can finally
retire as his babysitter.

130
00:08:32,860 --> 00:08:34,540
He's your problem now.

131
00:08:36,280 --> 00:08:38,570
No returns allowed!

132
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:40,120
I'm out.

133
00:08:45,500 --> 00:08:47,230
What does he mean, "He's your problem"?

134
00:08:49,010 --> 00:08:50,730
Oh, and tomorrow after school...

135
00:08:50,850 --> 00:08:52,250
Come by the student council office.

136
00:08:52,580 --> 00:08:54,040
I need your help with something.

137
00:09:00,150 --> 00:09:01,350
Yes!

138
00:09:01,720 --> 00:09:05,060
Finally, I don't have to clean
up Sara's messes anymore.

139
00:09:19,300 --> 00:09:27,300
(Fuu: I talked to Taiga-senpai today.)

140
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:31,500
(Sara: I see.)

141
00:09:31,520 --> 00:09:32,520
That's it?

142
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:49,200
(Fuu: Taiga-senpai is
really worried about you.)

143
00:09:58,060 --> 00:09:59,880
He left me on read!

144
00:10:08,700 --> 00:10:15,700
(Sara: Stop talking to Taiga.)

145
00:10:15,800 --> 00:10:19,800
(Sara: Sorry, I'm just a little jealous.)

146
00:10:34,600 --> 00:10:39,700
(Fuu: Come out to the balcony.)

147
00:11:06,530 --> 00:11:07,830
Knock, knock.

148
00:11:08,490 --> 00:11:09,910
Earth to Sara.

149
00:11:09,970 --> 00:11:11,170
Can you hear me?

150
00:11:21,540 --> 00:11:22,540
Fuu!

151
00:11:22,840 --> 00:11:23,840
That's dangerous.

152
00:11:35,910 --> 00:11:38,040
I had to make sure you were listening.

153
00:11:44,840 --> 00:11:45,840
I'm listening.

154
00:11:51,680 --> 00:11:52,680
So, tomorrow...

155
00:11:52,800 --> 00:11:55,010
Taiga-senpai asked me to help him out.

156
00:11:58,310 --> 00:11:59,310
Taiga?

157
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:02,000
Yeah.

158
00:12:02,353 --> 00:12:04,573
He used to be the student
council president, right?

159
00:12:04,740 --> 00:12:06,660
It's probably something
for the student council.

160
00:12:15,970 --> 00:12:17,260
That guy...

161
00:12:18,860 --> 00:12:19,860
Never mind.

162
00:12:20,030 --> 00:12:21,070
You don't have to go.

163
00:12:21,770 --> 00:12:23,010
I'll tell him no for you.

164
00:12:25,720 --> 00:12:28,730
Honestly, it's because of stuff like this
that everyone's afraid of you.

165
00:12:33,670 --> 00:12:34,870
Are you afraid of me too, Fuu?

166
00:12:38,870 --> 00:12:39,870
Not at all.

167
00:12:40,530 --> 00:12:42,450
That's why I think
everyone is being ridiculous.

168
00:12:46,160 --> 00:12:47,650
I don't care what they think.

169
00:13:00,080 --> 00:13:02,170
I'm only kind to you.

170
00:13:05,183 --> 00:13:08,203
Because I don't want you
to be afraid or avoid me.

171
00:13:11,260 --> 00:13:12,260
But...

172
00:13:12,530 --> 00:13:13,550
"Fuu" doesn't like that.

173
00:13:14,870 --> 00:13:15,870
Sara-senpai...

174
00:13:16,190 --> 00:13:17,590
You're actually such a nice person.

175
00:13:25,690 --> 00:13:27,890
You finally called yourself "Fuu."

176
00:14:12,020 --> 00:14:14,780
Ah, so you're the one
everyone's talking about.

177
00:14:16,630 --> 00:14:17,630
Talking about?

178
00:14:18,770 --> 00:14:19,890
Hey.

179
00:14:20,270 --> 00:14:22,330
You're dating Sara, right?

180
00:14:23,190 --> 00:14:24,190
Huh?

181
00:14:25,060 --> 00:14:26,060
Uh...

182
00:14:39,910 --> 00:14:41,550
How did you land someone like Sara?

183
00:14:42,730 --> 00:14:45,460
What's he like with you?

184
00:14:46,020 --> 00:14:47,220
Is he cold to you too?

185
00:14:49,310 --> 00:14:50,510
Well...

186
00:14:53,400 --> 00:14:54,400
Knock it off.

187
00:15:01,310 --> 00:15:03,520
Don't pick on your junior.

188
00:15:04,520 --> 00:15:05,850
We weren't picking on him.

189
00:15:06,210 --> 00:15:07,460
That's enough.

190
00:15:09,490 --> 00:15:11,030
Sara's getting angry.

191
00:15:20,720 --> 00:15:21,720
Maya, let's go.

192
00:15:21,760 --> 00:15:22,760
Okay.

193
00:15:37,630 --> 00:15:38,630
I'll help.

194
00:16:07,720 --> 00:16:09,720
Wait, Sara...

195
00:16:18,790 --> 00:16:19,790
Sara.

196
00:16:20,580 --> 00:16:22,150
Come here for a second.

197
00:16:29,750 --> 00:16:31,510
Just come here.

198
00:16:32,350 --> 00:16:33,850
Hurry up.

199
00:16:38,850 --> 00:16:39,850
What is it?

200
00:16:40,260 --> 00:16:41,260
Fuu is waiting for me.

201
00:16:45,200 --> 00:16:48,370
Are you really the Sara I know?

202
00:16:50,920 --> 00:16:53,760
You used to hate sharing food
with anyone else.

203
00:16:54,920 --> 00:16:56,230
But he's special.

204
00:16:58,490 --> 00:16:59,690
There you go again.

205
00:16:59,710 --> 00:17:00,710
Always with that line.

206
00:17:05,100 --> 00:17:06,500
You should go back to the hospital.

207
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:09,120
Your brain must still be
scrambled from the accident.

208
00:17:10,230 --> 00:17:11,430
Taiga.

209
00:17:11,920 --> 00:17:13,820
Do you know who you're talking to?

210
00:17:14,460 --> 00:17:16,050
Look, flirt all you want,

211
00:17:16,740 --> 00:17:19,140
but if "that person" finds out,
you're the one who'll pay...

212
00:17:19,460 --> 00:17:20,620
That's none of your business.

213
00:17:23,803 --> 00:17:25,023
Fine, I'm done.

214
00:17:26,570 --> 00:17:28,210
Don't blame me for whatever happens next.

215
00:18:31,820 --> 00:18:32,940
Aren't you going to kiss me?

216
00:18:37,890 --> 00:18:40,610
Kissing someone while they're
asleep is a bit much, don't you think?

217
00:18:46,790 --> 00:18:48,020
I'm already awake...

218
00:19:59,700 --> 00:20:00,700
Fuu?

219
00:20:02,060 --> 00:20:03,060
What's wrong?

220
00:20:05,080 --> 00:20:08,050
I was just thinking... I kissed someone
who already has a boyfriend again.

221
00:20:09,610 --> 00:20:12,250
But my boyfriend is Fuu,
no matter which world it is.

222
00:20:13,380 --> 00:20:14,380
Yeah.

223
00:20:15,100 --> 00:20:16,780
They have the same face and the same name.

224
00:20:17,090 --> 00:20:18,570
But they're different people.

225
00:20:29,170 --> 00:20:30,370
You didn't do anything wrong.

226
00:20:32,190 --> 00:20:33,430
I'm the one at fault.

227
00:20:56,490 --> 00:20:57,490
Good morning.

228
00:21:08,680 --> 00:21:09,680
Morning.

229
00:21:13,160 --> 00:21:14,160
Don't look at me.

230
00:21:14,290 --> 00:21:15,490
I just woke up.

231
00:21:18,170 --> 00:21:19,170
Why not?

232
00:21:19,840 --> 00:21:21,210
You're so cute.

233
00:21:47,610 --> 00:21:49,440
Are you going to keep ignoring me?

234
00:21:55,330 --> 00:21:56,530
You're so selfish.

235
00:21:57,000 --> 00:21:58,330
Just a little longer.

236
00:21:59,710 --> 00:22:00,710
It's okay.

237
00:22:00,910 --> 00:22:02,700
I like eating here.

238
00:22:07,340 --> 00:22:09,589
Have you ever wondered
what life would be like

239
00:22:09,590 --> 00:22:11,140
if we had never met?

240
00:22:13,390 --> 00:22:14,590
I probably

241
00:22:14,740 --> 00:22:15,940
wouldn't have made it.

242
00:22:18,530 --> 00:22:19,530
And neither would you.

243
00:22:20,330 --> 00:22:21,330
Hey.

244
00:22:21,730 --> 00:22:22,730
Promise me.

245
00:22:23,477 --> 00:22:24,816
Promise you won't leave me.

246
00:22:33,280 --> 00:22:34,950
You forgot your umbrella again.

247
00:22:38,190 --> 00:22:40,380
Because I knew you'd bring me one.

248
00:22:41,610 --> 00:22:43,499
I'll get into university first

249
00:22:43,500 --> 00:22:44,769
and wait for you there.

250
00:22:44,770 --> 00:22:46,440
I know you'll get in too.

251
00:22:46,870 --> 00:22:47,870
It's a promise, okay?

252
00:22:57,420 --> 00:23:00,410
Don't leave me. Stay by my side forever.

253
00:23:01,420 --> 00:23:03,520
I can't live without you anymore.

254
00:23:19,300 --> 00:23:20,500
How could I ever say that?

255
00:23:22,450 --> 00:23:23,450
Because

256
00:23:25,170 --> 00:23:26,460
I...

257
00:23:29,610 --> 00:23:30,610
Liar.

258
00:23:32,930 --> 00:23:35,410
Why did you lie and say
you were dating Naruka?

259
00:23:36,030 --> 00:23:37,030
Well,

260
00:23:37,260 --> 00:23:39,149
telling her I have a new girlfriend

261
00:23:39,150 --> 00:23:40,690
was the cleanest way
to break up, wasn't it?

262
00:23:40,700 --> 00:23:43,780
What if she tries to take it out on Naruka?

263
00:23:43,970 --> 00:23:45,499
- You should just die.
- That's terrifying.

264
00:23:45,500 --> 00:23:47,190
I get it. I'll apologize.

265
00:23:48,290 --> 00:23:49,290
Forgive me.

266
00:23:51,010 --> 00:23:52,010
Yutori.

267
00:23:52,020 --> 00:23:53,020
It's fine.

268
00:23:53,540 --> 00:23:56,610
Yutori will protect me, right?

269
00:23:58,880 --> 00:24:00,270
Don't let it happen again.

270
00:24:01,510 --> 00:24:02,510
Thanks.

271
00:24:04,300 --> 00:24:06,040
Oh, what about you, Fuu?

272
00:24:06,290 --> 00:24:08,690
How are things with Sara-senpai?

273
00:24:09,620 --> 00:24:11,790
It's nothing like that. We're not...

274
00:24:12,120 --> 00:24:13,120
Really?

275
00:24:13,130 --> 00:24:14,920
But I see you guys together all the time.

276
00:24:15,210 --> 00:24:16,960
I even saw you holding hands.

277
00:24:17,890 --> 00:24:19,840
Oh, speak of the devil.

278
00:24:20,520 --> 00:24:21,820
Isn't that Sara-senpai?

279
00:24:22,270 --> 00:24:23,770
Huh? Where?

280
00:24:24,860 --> 00:24:26,270
Just kidding!

281
00:24:27,490 --> 00:24:28,600
Stop it.

282
00:24:28,760 --> 00:24:32,330
There's no way it's nothing.
"There's really nothing..." Ow!

283
00:24:41,520 --> 00:24:42,520
Sara-senpai.

284
00:24:45,580 --> 00:24:46,580
Fuu.

285
00:24:57,620 --> 00:24:58,720
What are you doing?

286
00:25:38,503 --> 00:25:39,520
Well,

287
00:25:40,290 --> 00:25:41,490
I thought of something.

288
00:25:50,150 --> 00:25:52,510
Until you can get back to your world,

289
00:25:53,550 --> 00:25:55,000
I'll be your stand-in.

290
00:25:57,170 --> 00:25:58,170
A stand-in?

291
00:25:58,480 --> 00:25:59,480
Yeah.

292
00:26:00,786 --> 00:26:02,695
If the Fuu in your world
is anything like me,

293
00:26:02,720 --> 00:26:03,950
I'm sure he'd forgive me.

294
00:26:04,980 --> 00:26:07,100
It's better than you being lonely.

295
00:26:10,840 --> 00:26:13,390
Because you need your Fuu, right?

296
00:26:13,720 --> 00:26:14,720
Come on, smile.

297
00:26:15,500 --> 00:26:17,720
You look best when you're smiling.

298
00:26:28,110 --> 00:26:29,110
Thank you.

299
00:26:30,430 --> 00:26:33,010
For everything you've done...

300
00:26:38,700 --> 00:26:40,600
I know it's selfish,

301
00:26:43,530 --> 00:26:44,530
but

302
00:26:45,950 --> 00:26:47,770
I don't want to let go of either Fuu.

303
00:27:03,670 --> 00:27:05,740
I heard he's a student
at the same university.

304
00:27:05,940 --> 00:27:08,260
They've been spending a
lot of time together lately.

305
00:27:22,240 --> 00:27:24,670
He doesn't seem to understand

306
00:27:25,560 --> 00:27:26,690
exactly

307
00:27:27,480 --> 00:27:28,920
who he belongs to.

308
00:29:04,060 --> 00:29:05,170
Here, if you'd like some.

309
00:29:05,690 --> 00:29:06,690
Oh, my.

310
00:29:08,030 --> 00:29:10,660
Make sure to save one for him today, too.

311
00:29:11,310 --> 00:29:13,000
The special curry bread, right?

312
00:29:13,640 --> 00:29:14,640
I know, I know.
